well - view layer is sligtly different from what we get used to ;)
this time instead of just regular cs class we are using html pages integrated
with quite usefull technology called Razor which enable us injecting c# code between 
html tags. To discover more read about razor at general, then look what is the purpose of _ViewImports and ViewStart files ;)

https://www.tutorialsteacher.com/mvc/razor-syntax

Also, look how We are able to anchor existing controllers from the views 
perspective (look for specifics tags in a html element ;) this is done with a help 
of so called html helpers

https://www.tutorialsteacher.com/mvc/html-helpers